Wlaz\u0142y]]\n* '''2010\u2013present''' {{flagicon|POL}} [[Karol K\u0142os]]\n* '''2017\u2013present''' {{flagicon|IRN}} [[Milad Ebadipour]]\n* '''2017\u2013present''' {{flagicon|POL}} [[Grzegorz \u0141omacz]]\n* '''2018\u2013present''' {{flagicon|POL}} [[Artur Szalpuk]]\n* '''2018\u2013present''' {{flagicon|POL}} [[Jakub Kochanowski]]\n* '''2019\u2013present''' {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Du\u0161an Petkovi\u0107 (volleyball)|Du\u0161an Petkovi\u0107]]\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Volleyball in Poland]]\n* [[Sports in Poland]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.skra.pl/ Official website] {{in lang|pl|en|ru}}\n\n{{commons category|Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w}}\n{{Polish Champions of men's volleyball}}\n{{PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w Seasons}}\n{{Polish Men's Volleyball League}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Skra Belchatow}}\n[[Category:Polish volleyball clubs]]\n[[Category:PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w| ]]\n[[Category:PGE Skra Be\u0142chat\u00f3w seasons| ]]\n", "name_user": "Maister1921", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PGE_Skra_Be%C5%82chat%C3%B3w"}
{"title_page": "Tridevi", "text_new": "{{short description|Hindu combining of three goddesses into one}}\n{{Infobox deity<!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Hindu mythology-->\n| type = Hindu\n| image =File:Supreme form durga.jpg\n| caption = triple deity personified\n| consort = [[Trimurti]], specifically\n* [[Brahma]], consort of Saraswati\n* [[Vishnu]], consort of Lakshmi\n* [[Shiva]], consort of Parvati\n| name = Tridevi\n| Devanagari = \u0924\u094d\u0930\u093f\u0926\u0947\u0935\u0940\n| Sanskrit_transliteration = {{IAST|tridev\u012b}}\n| affiliation = [[Saraswati]], [[Lakshmi]] and [[Parvati]];\n[[Devi]], [[Shakti]]\n| abode = \n*[[Satyaloka]], abode of Saraswati \n*[[Vaikunth]], abode of Lakshmi\n*[[Kailash]], abode of Parvati\n| mantra = Om Trideviyay Namah\n| god_of=Creation, preservation, and destruction\n| mount=\n* Swan, mount of Saraswati\n* Owl, mount of Lakshmi\n* Lion, mount of Parvati\n}}\n{{Hinduism}} \n{{Saktism}}\nThe '''Tridevi''' ({{lang-en|three goddesses}}; [[Sanskrit]]: \u0924\u094d\u0930\u093f\u0926\u0947\u0935\u0940, ''{{IAST|tridev\u012b}}'') is a concept in [[Hinduism]] joining a [[Triad (religious)|triad]] of eminent goddesses either as a feminine version of the [[Trimurti]] or as consorts of a masculine Trimurti, depending on the denomination. This triad is typically [[Anthropomorphism|personified]] by the [[Hindu]] goddesses [[Saraswati]], [[Lakshmi]], and [[Parvati]]. In [[Shaktism]], these triune goddesses are the manifestations of goddess [[Yogmaya]] also known by the names of [[Adi Parashakti]], ''[[Devi]]''.\n\nIn the [[Navaratri]] (\"nine nights\") festival, \"the Goddess is worshiped in three forms. During the first three nights, [[Parvati]] is revered, then Lakshmi on the fourth, fifth and sixth nights, and finally Saraswati until the ninth night.\"<ref>[http://www.hinduismtoday.com/modules/smartsection/item.php?itemid=3073 \"Navaratri\", in ''Hinduism Today''] magazine, October/November/December 2008.</ref>\n\n== As the feminine Trimurti ==\n[[File:MahaKali MahaLakshmi MahaSaraswati.jpg|thumb|[[Kali|Maha Kali]], [[Lakshmi]] and [[Saraswati]]]]\nWhereas in androcentric denominations of Hinduism the feminine Tridevi goddesses are relegated as consorts and auxiliary deities to the more eminent masculine [[Trimurti]] gods, in the [[Shaktism|Shaktidharma]] denomination the feminine Tridevi goddesses are given the eminent roles of [[Mahasaraswati|Creatrix (Mahasarasvati)]], [[Mahalaxmi|Preservatrix (Mahalaxmi)]], and [[Mahakali|Destructrix (Mahakali)]], with the masculine Trimurti gods being relegated as the auxiliary deities as agents of the feminine Tridevi.\n\n== As consorts of the Trimurti ==\n[[Saraswati]] is the goddess of learning, arts, and cultural fulfillment, as well as consort of [[Brahma]], the creator. She is cosmic intelligence, cosmic consciousness, and cosmic knowledge.\n\n[[Lakshmi]] is the goddess of wealth, fertility, and material fulfillment, as well as consort of [[Vishnu]], the maintainer or preserver. However, Lakshmi does not signify mere material wealth, but also abstract prosperity, such as glory, magnificence, joy, exaltation, and greatness.\n\n[[Parvati]], or in her demon-fighting aspect, [[Kali]], is the goddess of power, beauty, love, and spiritual fulfillment, as well as consort of [[Shiva]], the destroyer of evil or transformer. She also represents the transformational power of divinity, the power that dissolves the multiplicity of the Hindu gods into their unity. She is a direct incarnation of [[Adi Parashakti]].\n\n==Importance of Tridevi==\n[[Shakti]] or Vimarsh is the power that is latent in pure consciousness, required to reach pure consciousness and essential to create, sustain and destroy. Just as [[Energy]] can never be created nor be destroyed, but changes from one form to another; [[Devi]] took many incarnations to do different tasks. God is both male and female. But all different forms of energy or powers of God are with the Trimurti in the form of [[Mahasaraswati]], [[Mahalakshmi]], and [[Mahakali]]. That is to say, a non-dimensional God creates this world through Srishti-Shakti (Mahasaraswati or Sound or knowledge), preserves through Sthiti-Shakti (Mahalakshmi or Light or resources), and destroys through Samhara-Shakti (Mahakali or Heat or Strength). It is also seen that God cannot create, generate or destroy because God does not possess any attribute. So True Energy or Adi Shakti does everything on God's behalf.\n\n==The Tridevi outside India==\nVia [[Buddhism_in_Japan|Buddhism]] and [[Shinbutsu-sh\u016bg\u014d|syncretism]] with Japanese [[Kami|Shinto deities]], the Tridevi entered Japanese mythology as the goddesses [[Benzaiten|Benzaitennyo \u5f01\u8ca1\u5929\u5973 (Sarasvati)]], [[Kissh\u014dten|Kisshoutennyo \u5409\u7965\u5929\u5973 (Laxmi)]], and [[Daikokuten#Goddess_Daikokutennyo|Daikokutennyo \u5927\u9ed2\u5929\u5973 (Mahakali)]].\n\n==See also==\n{{col div|colwidth=20em}}\n*[[Devi]]\n*[[Seven_Lucky_Gods|Fukujin (\u798f\u795e) deities]] \n*[[Japanese_Buddhist_pantheon#Level_4:_Heavenly_deities_.28Ten-bu.29|Buddhist Tenbu (\u5929\u90e8) deities]]\n*[[Navratri]]\n*[[Trimurti]]\n*[[Trinity]]\n*[[Triple deities]]\n*[[Bindudham|Bindudham (a temple of Tridevi)]]\n*[[Mahalakshmi_Temple,_Mumbai#Inside|Mahalaxmi Temple (Mumbai)]]\n{{colend}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n[http://mahalakshmi-temple.com/images/mahalaxmi_mata_larg.jpg Tridevi statues in the Mahalaxmi temple in Mumbai]\n\n{{HinduMythology}}\n{{Hindudharma}}\n{{Hinduism footer small}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Hindu philosophical concepts]]\n[[Category:Names of God in Hinduism]]\n[[Category:Triple goddesses]]\n[[Category:Hindu goddesses]]\n[[Category:Feminist theology]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Hindu combining of three goddesses into one}}\n{{Infobox deity<!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Hindu mythology-->\n| type = Hindu\n| image =File:Supreme form durga.jpg\n| caption = triple deity personified\n| consort = [[Trimurti]], specifically\n* [[Brahma]], consort of Saraswati\n* [[Vishnu]], consort of Lakshmi\n* [[Shiva]], consort of Parvati\n| name = Tridevi\n| Devanagari = \u0924\u094d\u0930\u093f\u0926\u0947\u0935\u0940\n| Sanskrit_transliteration = {{IAST|tridev\u012b}}\n| affiliation = [[Saraswati]], [[Lakshmi]] and [[Parvati]];\n[[Devi]], [[Shakti]]\n| abode = \n*[[Satyaloka]], abode of Saraswati \n*[[Vaikunth]], abode of Lakshmi\n*[[Kailash]], abode of Parvati\n| mantra = Om Trideviyay Namah\n| god_of=Creation, preservation, and destruction\n| mount=\n* Swan, mount of Saraswati\n* Owl, mount of Lakshmi\n* Lion, mount of Parvati\n}}\n{{Hinduism}} \n{{Saktism}}\nThe '''Tridevi''' ({{lang-en|three goddesses}}; [[Sanskrit]]: \u0924\u094d\u0930\u093f\u0926\u0947\u0935\u0940, ''{{IAST|tridev\u012b}}'') is a concept in [[Hinduism]] joining a [[Triad (religious)|triad]] of eminent goddesses either as a feminine version of the [[Trimurti]] or as consorts of a masculine Trimurti, depending on the denomination. This triad is typically [[Anthropomorphism|personified]] by the [[Hindu]] goddesses [[Saraswati]], [[Lakshmi]], and [[Parvati]]. In [[Shaktism]], these triune goddesses are the manifestations of goddess [[Yogmaya]] also known by the names of [[Adi Parashakti]], ''[[Devi]]''.\n\nIn the [[Navaratri]] (\"nine nights\") festival, \"the Goddess is worshiped in three forms. During the first three nights, [[Parvati]] is revered, then Lakshmi on the fourth, fifth and sixth nights, and finally Saraswati until the ninth night.\"<ref>[http://www.hinduismtoday.com/modules/smartsection/item.php?itemid=3073 \"Navaratri\", in ''Hinduism Today''] magazine, October/November/December 2008.</ref>\n\n== As the feminine Trimurti ==\n[[File:MahaKali MahaLakshmi MahaSaraswati.jpg|thumb|[[Kali|Maha Kali]], [[Lakshmi]] and [[Saraswati]]]]\nWhereas in androcentric denominations of Hinduism the feminine Tridevi goddesses are relegated as consorts and auxiliary deities to the more eminent masculine [[Trimurti]] gods, in the [[Shaktism|Shaktidharma]] denomination the feminine Tridevi goddesses are given the eminent roles of [[Mahasaraswati|Create (Mahasarasvati)]], [[Mahalaxmi|Preserve (Mahalaxmi)]], and [[Mahakali|Destruct (Mahakali)]], with the masculine Trimurti gods being relegated as the auxiliary deities as agents of the feminine Tridevi.\n\n== As consorts of the Trimurti ==\n[[Saraswati]] is the goddess of learning, arts, and cultural fulfillment, as well as consort of [[Brahma]], the creator. She is cosmic intelligence, cosmic consciousness, and cosmic knowledge.\n\n[[Lakshmi]] is the goddess of wealth, fertility, and material fulfillment, as well as consort of [[Vishnu]], the maintainer or preserver. However, Lakshmi does not signify mere material wealth, but also abstract prosperity, such as glory, magnificence, joy, exaltation, and greatness.\n\n[[Parvati]], or in her demon-fighting aspect, [[Kali]], is the goddess of power, beauty, love, and spiritual fulfillment, as well as consort of [[Shiva]], the destroyer of evil or transformer. She also represents the transformational power of divinity, the power that dissolves the multiplicity of the Hindu gods into their unity. She is a direct incarnation of [[Adi Parashakti]].\n\n==Importance of Tridevi==\n[[Shakti]] or Vimarsh is the power that is latent in pure consciousness, required to reach pure consciousness and essential to create, sustain and destroy. Just as [[Energy]] can never be created nor be destroyed, but changes from one form to another; [[Devi]] took many incarnations to do different tasks. God is both male and female. But all different forms of energy or powers of God are with the Trimurti in the form of [[Mahasaraswati]], [[Mahalakshmi]], and [[Mahakali]]. That is to say, a non-dimensional God creates this world through Srishti-Shakti (Mahasaraswati or Sound or knowledge), preserves through Sthiti-Shakti (Mahalakshmi or Light or resources), and destroys through Samhara-Shakti (Mahakali or Heat or Strength). It is also seen that God cannot create, generate or destroy because God does not possess any attribute. So True Energy or Adi Shakti does everything on God's behalf.\n\n==The Tridevi outside India==\nVia [[Buddhism_in_Japan|Buddhism]] and [[Shinbutsu-sh\u016bg\u014d|syncretism]] with Japanese [[Kami|Shinto deities]], the Tridevi entered Japanese mythology as the goddesses [[Benzaiten|Benzaitennyo \u5f01\u8ca1\u5929\u5973 (Sarasvati)]], [[Kissh\u014dten|Kisshoutennyo \u5409\u7965\u5929\u5973 (Laxmi)]], and [[Daikokuten#Goddess_Daikokutennyo|Daikokutennyo \u5927\u9ed2\u5929\u5973 (Mahakali)]].\n\n==See also==\n{{col div|colwidth=20em}}\n*[[Devi]]\n*[[Seven_Lucky_Gods|Fukujin (\u798f\u795e) deities]] \n*[[Japanese_Buddhist_pantheon#Level_4:_Heavenly_deities_.28Ten-bu.29|Buddhist Tenbu (\u5929\u90e8) deities]]\n*[[Navratri]]\n*[[Trimurti]]\n*[[Trinity]]\n*[[Triple deities]]\n*[[Bindudham|Bindudham (a temple of Tridevi)]]\n*[[Mahalakshmi_Temple,_Mumbai#Inside|Mahalaxmi Temple (Mumbai)]]\n{{colend}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n[http://mahalakshmi-temple.com/images/mahalaxmi_mata_larg.jpg Tridevi statues in the Mahalaxmi temple in Mumbai]\n\n{{HinduMythology}}\n{{Hindudharma}}\n{{Hinduism footer small}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Hindu philosophical concepts]]\n[[Category:Names of God in Hinduism]]\n[[Category:Triple goddesses]]\n[[Category:Hindu goddesses]]\n[[Category:Feminist theology]]\n", "name_user": "Sciovore", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAs the feminine Trimurti:Corrected grammar", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tridevi"}
{"title_page": "2019 Laguna Beechcraft King Air crash", "text_new": "{{Infobox aircraft occurrence\n| image = Beechcraft King Air 350 PR-OTG (15905068624).jpg\n| image_upright = 1.2\n| alt = \n| caption = A Beechcraft King Air 350 similar to the aircraft involved\n| occurrence_type = Accident\n| date = {{start date|2019|09|01|df=y}}\n| summary = Crashed during a medical evacuation flight; Under investigation\n| site = Agojo Resort, [[Pansol]], [[Calamba, Laguna]], [[Philippines]]\n| coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LON|type:event|display = inline,title}} -->\n| total_fatalities = 9\n| total_injuries = 2\n| occupants = 9\n| passengers = 7\n| crew = 2\n| fatalities = 9\n| survivors = 0\n| aircraft_type = [[Beechcraft Super King Air|Beechcraft B300 King Air 350]]\n| aircraft_name = \n| operator = [[Lionair (Philippines)]]\n| tail_number = RP-C2296<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ranter |first1=Harro |url=https://aviation-safety.net/database/record.php?id=20190901-0 |title=Accident Description for RP-C2296 |website=[[Aviation Safety Network]] |date=1 September 2019 |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref>\n| origin = [[Dipolog Airport]], [[Zamboanga del Norte]], [[Philippines]]\n| destination = [[Ninoy Aquino International Airport]], [[Manila]], [[Philippines]]\n| ground_fatalities = 0\n| ground_injuries = 2\n}}\n\nOn 1 September 2019, a [[Beechcraft Super King Air|Beechcraft King Air 350]] operated by [[Lionair (Philippines)|Lionair]] crashed into a private resort in [[Calamba, Laguna]], [[Philippines]] while performing a medical evacuation flight from [[Dipolog City]], [[Zamboanga del Norte]], [[Philippines]] to [[Manila]], [[Philippines]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/09/01/19/plane-crashes-in-calamba-laguna |title=Several killed as plane crashes in Calamba, Laguna |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[ABS-CBN News]] |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref> All nine occupants aboard were killed in the crash.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gulfnews.com/amp/world/asia/philippines/9-killed-in-philippines-air-ambulance-crash-near-manila-authorities-1.1567341864411 |title=9 killed in Philippines air-ambulance crash near Manila: authorities |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[Gulf News]] |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== Accident ==\n\nAccording to the [[Civil Aviation Authority of the Philippines]], the aircraft, which originated from the [[Dipolog Airport]] in [[Zamboanga del Norte]], was on a medical evacuation flight to [[Manila]] when it disappeared on radar at around 3:10 p.m while flying 25 nautical miles from Manila. It crashed into a private resort at [[Pansol]], [[Calamba, Laguna]], killing all nine occupants aboard.<ref name=\"rappler.com\">{{cite web |url=https://rappler.com/nation/239047-light-plane-crash-calamba-laguna-september-1-2019 |author=<!--Not stated--> |title=9 dead as small plane crashes into Calamba resort in Laguna |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[Rappler.com]] |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref> Among the dead were a patient being transported and his wife.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://globalnation.inquirer.net/179643/new-zealand-couple-among-dead-in-laguna-lightplane-crash/amp |author=<!--Not stated--> |title=New Zealand couple among dead in Laguna lightplane crash |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[Inquirer.net]] |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref> Two people who were inside the resort were injured. \n\n== Investigation ==\n\nThe [[Civil Aviation Authority of the Philippines]] and the Aircraft Accident Investigation and Inquiry Board started an investigation into the accident. The CAAP said that it has substantial information to determine the cause, but according to plane crash investigator Harry Pandero, there is a possibility that the crash was caused by either pilot error or the inclement weather.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mindanaodailynews.com/news/front-page/todays-top-stories/pilot-error-bad-weather-eyed-in-laguna-plane-crash-probe |title=Pilot error, bad weather eyed in Laguna plane crash probe |date=4 September 2019 |work=Mindanao Daily News |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2019/9/1/plane-crash-Pansol-Laguna.html |title=9 fatalities in air ambulance plane crash in Laguna resort named |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[CNN Philippines]] |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2019 in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in 2019]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox aircraft occurrence\n| image = Beechcraft King Air 350 PR-OTG (15905068624).jpg\n| image_upright = 1.2\n| alt = \n| caption = A Beechcraft King Air 350 similar to the aircraft involved\n| occurrence_type = Accident\n| date = {{start date|2019|09|01|df=y}}\n| summary = Crashed during a medical evacuation flight; Under investigation\n| site = Agojo Resort, [[Pansol]], [[Calamba, Laguna]], [[Philippines]]\n| coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LON|type:event|display = inline,title}} -->\n| total_fatalities = 9\n| total_injuries = 2\n| occupants = 9\n| passengers = 7\n| crew = 2\n| fatalities = 9\n| survivors = 0\n| aircraft_type = [[Beechcraft Super King Air|Beechcraft B300 King Air 350]]\n| aircraft_name = \n| operator = [[Lionair (Philippines)]]\n| tail_number = RP-C2296<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ranter |first1=Harro |url=https://aviation-safety.net/database/record.php?id=20190901-0 |title=Accident Description for RP-C2296 |website=[[Aviation Safety Network]] |date=1 September 2019 |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref>\n| origin = [[Dipolog Airport]], [[Zamboanga del Norte]], [[Philippines]]\n| destination = [[Ninoy Aquino International Airport]], [[Manila]], [[Philippines]]\n| ground_fatalities = 0\n| ground_injuries = 2\n}}\n\nOn 1 September 2019, a [[Beechcraft Super King Air|Beechcraft King Air 350]] operated by [[Lionair (Philippines)|Lionair]] crashed into a private resort in [[Calamba, Laguna]], [[Philippines]] while performing a medical evacuation flight from [[Dipolog City]], [[Zamboanga del Norte]], [[Philippines]] to [[Manila]], [[Philippines]].<ref name=\"abscbn\">{{cite web |url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/news/09/01/19/plane-crashes-in-calamba-laguna |title=Several killed as plane crashes in Calamba, Laguna |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[ABS-CBN News]] |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref> All nine occupants aboard were killed in the crash.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gulfnews.com/amp/world/asia/philippines/9-killed-in-philippines-air-ambulance-crash-near-manila-authorities-1.1567341864411 |title=9 killed in Philippines air-ambulance crash near Manila: authorities |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[Gulf News]] |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== Accident ==\n\nAccording to the [[Civil Aviation Authority of the Philippines]], the aircraft, which originated from the [[Dipolog Airport]] in [[Zamboanga del Norte]], was on a medical evacuation flight to [[Manila]] when it disappeared on radar at around 3:10 p.m while flying 25 nautical miles from Manila. It crashed into a private resort at [[Pansol]], [[Calamba, Laguna]], killing all nine occupants aboard.<ref name=\"rappler.com\">{{cite web |url=https://rappler.com/nation/239047-light-plane-crash-calamba-laguna-september-1-2019 |author=<!--Not stated--> |title=9 dead as small plane crashes into Calamba resort in Laguna |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[Rappler.com]] |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref> Among the dead were a patient being transported and his wife.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://globalnation.inquirer.net/179643/new-zealand-couple-among-dead-in-laguna-lightplane-crash/amp |author=<!--Not stated--> |title=New Zealand couple among dead in Laguna lightplane crash |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[Inquirer.net]] |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref> A mother and son who were inside the resort were injured.<ref name=\"abscbn\"/>\n\n== Investigation ==\n\nThe [[Civil Aviation Authority of the Philippines]] and the Aircraft Accident Investigation and Inquiry Board started an investigation into the accident. The CAAP said that it has substantial information to determine the cause, but according to plane crash investigator Harry Pandero, there is a possibility that the crash was caused by either pilot error or the inclement weather.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mindanaodailynews.com/news/front-page/todays-top-stories/pilot-error-bad-weather-eyed-in-laguna-plane-crash-probe |title=Pilot error, bad weather eyed in Laguna plane crash probe |date=4 September 2019 |work=Mindanao Daily News |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2019/9/1/plane-crash-Pansol-Laguna.html |title=9 fatalities in air ambulance plane crash in Laguna resort named |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[CNN Philippines]] |accessdate=24 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2019 in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Aviation accidents and incidents in 2019]]\n", "name_user": "BERTD427", "label": "safe", "comment": "Corrected", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_Laguna_Beechcraft_King_Air_crash"}
